/*
  Netlify SPA routing fix.
  Without this, any URL that isn't the root (e.g. /admin/login)
  returns a 404 on page refresh because Netlify looks for actual
  files at those paths. This rule rewrites everything to index.html
  so React Router can handle the routing on the client side.
*/
/*  path    file          status  */
/*    ↓       ↓             ↓    */
    /       /index.html   200
